COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.NOT_FOUND
test: Get your head on straight! Command `{commandName}` does not exist.

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.PREFIX.VIEW.SHORTDESC
test: Shows the defined prefixes and tells which one you should use.

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.PREFIX.VIEW.CORRECT.DEFAULT
test: Since neither server nor user prefix has been defined, use the default prefix `{prefix}`

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.PREFIX.VIEW.CORRECT.SERVER
test: Since you have not defined your own prefix, but the server has, use the server prefix `{prefix}`

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.PREFIX.VIEW.CORRECT.USER
test: Since you have defined your own prefix, use that one (`{prefix}`)

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.PREFIX.USER.SHORTDESC
test: Changes the personal prefix of the user.

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.PREFIX.USER.CHANGED
test: **{user}**, you have changed your prefix to `{prefix}`

COMMAND.TEST.NAME: COMMAND.ARGUMENT_CONV.ERROR
test: Unable to convert `{argument}` to a number. Make sure your input is correct and try again.
